{
  "stem": "13469.2",
  "chunk_idx": 15,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Young children didn't have to have them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I can't remember now whether I and Ruti had them, at what age you started with them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But I think we did have them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But the actual ones that we still have here, today, for you are, are the identity cards of my two paternal grandparents.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And there, you can see very clearly their photograph, their fingerprint, and a big J by the side of their name.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And also, you can see that their names were Josef and Meta.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But the Germans made us-- all, all Jews had to take on the name of 'Israel' if you were male and 'Sarah' if you were female.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I mean, I never understood the reason for this.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I mean, a ridiculous idea kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I don't know what it meant.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Nobody called them Israel or Sarah.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But on this identity card, it's typed, Josef.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And in ink, it's written, Israel, by the side of it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And, and the same for-- Meta, typed, Sarah, in ink written by the side of it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So that was obviously added later on to the identity cards, when everybody had to carry these identity cards with a J.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And they had to take these names of Israel and Sarah.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
